reviewText: the photography is stunning but it is the music that makes this film a stand out! songs from bands like witch and dungen match up really well with the action on the screen.

I like it and I'll watch it again.  But it's not great.  I bought it because I really liked the format of Volcom's "Walrus Dreams," but this wasn't nearly as good.  I expected more from Volcom, like some artsy side stuff.  The one thing that was good about it was it wasn't bombarded with rails.
